@page
@model AboutModel
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "About - SWORD Intelligence";
}

<div class="page-header">
    <div class="container">
        <h1>About SWORD Intelligence</h1>
        <p class="lead">ASP.NET Core Implementation</p>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="container">
    <section class="content-section">
        <h2>Technology Overview</h2>
        <p>
            This is a sophisticated reimplementation of the SWORD Intelligence platform using
            <strong>ASP.NET Core 8.0</strong> with <strong>esoteric architectural choices</strong>
            that showcase modern .NET capabilities while maintaining the original aesthetic.
        </p>

        <div class="tech-grid">
            <div class="tech-item">
                <h3>ðŸ”· Hybrid Architecture</h3>
                <p>Combines Razor Pages, Blazor Server, MVC, and Minimal APIs in one application</p>
            </div>

            <div class="tech-item">
                <h3>ðŸ”· F# Cryptography</h3>
                <p>All cryptographic operations implemented in F# for functional purity</p>
            </div>

            <div class="tech-item">
                <h3>ðŸ”· Post-Quantum Security</h3>
                <p>ML-KEM-1024 and ML-DSA-87 using BouncyCastle</p>
            </div>

            <div class="tech-item">
                <h3>ðŸ”· Real-time SignalR</h3>
                <p>WebSocket messaging with Redis backplane for scaling</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="content-section">
        <h2>Architecture Highlights</h2>
        <ul class="feature-list">
            <li><strong>Vertical Slice Architecture:</strong> Features organized by capability</li>
            <li><strong>CQRS-lite with MediatR:</strong> Separated read/write models</li>
            <li><strong>Entity Framework Core:</strong> PostgreSQL with C# record types</li>
            <li><strong>Custom Middleware Pipeline:</strong> Security, logging, threat detection</li>
            <li><strong>Background Services:</strong> OSINT sync, dead drop monitoring</li>
            <li><strong>Distributed Caching:</strong> Redis for performance and scalability</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="content-section">
        <h2>Security Features</h2>
        <ul class="feature-list">
            <li>FIDO2/WebAuthn hardware key authentication</li>
            <li>Multi-factor authentication with TOTP</li>
            <li>JWT Bearer tokens with refresh rotation</li>
            <li>Post-quantum hybrid encryption</li>
            <li>End-to-end encrypted messaging</li>
            <li>Canary token intrusion detection</li>
            <li>Tamper-evident audit logging</li>
            <li>CSP headers with dynamic nonces</li>
            <li>Rate limiting with distributed cache</li>
            <li>Attack pattern detection middleware</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="content-section">
        <h2>Esoteric Design Choices</h2>
        <p>This implementation makes several unconventional architectural decisions to showcase advanced .NET patterns:</p>

        <div class="design-choices">
            <div class="choice-card">
                <h4>1. F# for Cryptography</h4>
                <p>
                    All cryptographic operations are implemented in a separate F# project.
                    Functional programming provides immutability and type safety for security-critical code.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="choice-card">
                <h4>2. Record Types Everywhere</h4>
                <p>
                    All DTOs and database entities use C# record types for structural equality
                    and immutability, reducing bugs and improving testability.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="choice-card">
                <h4>3. Hybrid UI Framework</h4>
                <p>
                    Public pages use Razor Pages, the portal uses Blazor Server, APIs use MVC controllers,
                    and some endpoints use Minimal APIs - showcasing all ASP.NET paradigms.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="choice-card">
                <h4>4. SignalR + Redis Backplane</h4>
                <p>
                    Real-time messaging uses SignalR with Redis pub/sub, enabling horizontal
                    scaling across multiple servers while maintaining WebSocket connections.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="content-section">
        <h2>Get Started</h2>
        <div class="cta-section">
            <a href="/portal/login" class="btn btn-primary">Access Portal</a>
            <a href="/api/health" class="btn btn-secondary">API Health</a>
        </div>
    </section>
</div>

